15/02/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- A Cambodian-registered ship carrying coal sank in the Black Sea off the Bosporus in heavy weather on Friday (13 February), taking 21 sailors with it. 
Authorities in Sofia announced that a Bulgarian firm had managed the vessel and at least 18 of the seamen were Bulgarians from Varna. 
Searchers have found no survivors. 
(Reuters, AFP, AP, BNT, bTV - 14/02/04)
